    <p class="text-gray-300">Form of v(X): We show that for all  <span class="math">j \\in [m]</span> ,  <span class="math">v_j^{-1}</span>  is a root of  <span class="math">z_I(X)</span> . In other words, there exists a map col:  <span class="math">[m] \\mapsto [k]</span>  such that for all  <span class="math">j \\in [m]</span> ,  <span class="math">v_j^{-1} = \\xi_{\\operatorname{col}(j)}</span> . Indeed, define  <span class="math">J = \\{j : v_j^{-1} \\notin \\mathbb{H}_I\\}</span> , and the set  <span class="math">V = \\{v_j : j \\in J\\}</span> . We assume for contradiction that there is some  <span class="math">v_j^{-1}</span>  that is not a root of  <span class="math">z_I(X)</span> , which means that V is not empty. Then,</p>

